    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Turpin</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Seward</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">[Extract.]</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 45.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                    States</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 27, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>The President has promised me to issue instructions to all <hi rend="italic">comandantes de puerto</hi> of the republic prohibiting
                            admission of all vessels under that [the confedate] flag into its ports,
                            except in cases of distress. I could not obtain from him their complete
                            denunciation as pirates.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have the honor, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. A. TURPIN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
